sect1:
Installing Gettext-&gettext-version;



The Gettext package contains utilities for internationalization and
localization. These allow programs to be compiled with Native Language Support
(NLS), enabling them to output messages in the user's native language.

&buildtime; &gettext-time;
&diskspace; &gettext-compsize;

&aa-gettext-down;
&aa-gettext-dep;

 
 


Installation of Gettext


Prepare Gettext for compilation:

./configure --prefix=/usr


Compile the package:

make


To have the results tested, issue:
make check. This takes a very long time, around
7 SBUs.


And install the package:

make install



